@perrette 

For the "algorithm" of FoBiS.py... I have to accurately check, but I think that is as you depicted:

+ FoBiS.py parse each source files it found:
  - tag the source as to be one of:
      * program;
      * module;
      * included file;
      * a non-module library (old Fortran file with a messy of procedures...);
  - construct the dependency of each parsed filed;
  - build its target (or all program it had found);

A a consequence the other two steps you suggest is done as you said:

+ from the computed hierarchy build the makefile (that is probably now bugged);
+ use make for testing FoBiS.py correctness.

