The reason `(?!
)` is needed is due to backtracking. Normally an atomic group would match `
`, and the engine would not be allowed to backtrack to make the match "fit" (match `` then `
`).  Re, since it doesn't support atomic groups, will backtrack, so `(?!
)` prevents it from ignoring the fact that `
` is required to be matched as a pair.

