@maikhoepfel I think you're confused–otherwise I'm missing something. First of all, we're talking about the `settings.py` file, right? "setup.py" is not a Django convention I know of.

In Django, the `INSTALLED_APPS` entry in `settings.py` is where you specify which Python modules you want your app to use, but it expects those modules to already be available in your virtualenv.

`requirements.txt` is what you use to make the modules available in your virtualenv! You need to specify `django-tweaks

